abstract: >
  A structured, literature-based multimodal and opioid-free anesthesia
  framework for robot-assisted total knee arthroplasty (rTKA). This
  repository defines three standardized anesthesia pathways (OFIA with
  ACB/IPACK, OFIA without blocks, and conventional opioid-inclusive
  anesthesia) and integrates OR readiness checklists, preoperative
  assessment tools, patient counseling scripts, intraoperative protocols,
  flowcharts, PACU handoff templates, surgeon one-page summaries, and a
  curated 2023â€“2025 evidence base. Designed as an educational and
  quality-improvement oriented protocol design project rather than a
  validated institutional order set.

